WEBVTT

00:00:29.238 --> 00:00:33.082
In some places, you can tell what time of
year it is by which flowers are in bloom.

00:00:35.481 --> 00:00:38.747
In Yokohama, it's which boats
you see passing through the harbor.

00:00:42.287 --> 00:00:47.550
Only, there are more and more of them now
since Tokyo was awarded the '64 Summer Olympics.

00:00:50.352 --> 00:00:53.589
We have a great view of the
boats from my house on Poppy Hill.

00:00:56.740 --> 00:00:58.691
Actually, it's my grandmother's house.

00:01:05.097 --> 00:01:07.777
But with my father gone and my mother studying in America,

00:01:08.610 --> 00:01:11.363
it's my job to cook and do laundry for our boarders

00:01:12.033 --> 00:01:14.340
and look after my little brother and sister.

00:01:17.519 --> 00:01:22.906
Ever since the wars, it seems the whole country is
eager to get rid of the old and make way for the new.

00:01:24.363 --> 00:01:27.114
But some of us aren't so ready to let go of the past, and

00:01:28.192 --> 00:01:31.122
sometimes the past is not ready let go of us either.

00:03:16.379 --> 00:03:17.839
Good morning, Umi!

00:03:17.839 --> 00:03:19.174
Good morning, Miss Aori.

00:03:19.396 --> 00:03:20.780
Is Sora up yet?

00:03:20.805 --> 00:03:22.461
Hmm, wouldn't that be a miracle?

00:03:22.891 --> 00:03:23.883
Good morning.

00:03:23.920 --> 00:03:24.578
Good morning, Miki.

00:03:24.594 --> 00:03:25.320
Morning.

00:03:26.023 --> 00:03:26.758
Ah.

00:03:27.797 --> 00:03:30.125
So, late night at the hospital again, Miki?

00:03:30.141 --> 00:03:30.695
Yep.

00:03:31.219 --> 00:03:32.602
And another one tonight.

00:03:33.289 --> 00:03:35.938
If you'd like, I can save dinner for you.

00:03:36.171 --> 00:03:37.725
Oh, you're a saint.

00:03:38.078 --> 00:03:39.789
What would we do without Umi?

00:03:40.594 --> 00:03:41.773
What will I do without...

00:03:41.789 --> 00:03:42.468
Hey, sis.

00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:44.062
I got another hole in my sock.

00:03:44.250 --> 00:03:46.008
Just leave it beside the sewing machine.

00:03:46.194 --> 00:03:47.913
That boy has holes in his head.

00:03:47.930 --> 00:03:49.023
Hey, I heard that.

00:03:49.539 --> 00:03:50.514
Two eggs, please.

00:03:50.538 --> 00:03:51.594
One is enough for you.

00:03:52.609 --> 00:03:55.055
Well, I've got sports today, so pack a big lunch.

00:03:55.086 --> 00:03:56.836
Is there a hole in your stomach too?

00:03:56.861 --> 00:03:57.642
Ha ha.

00:03:58.246 --> 00:03:58.906
Here, Riku.

00:03:58.922 --> 00:03:59.722
Have my eggs.

00:03:59.754 --> 00:04:00.213
Yes!

00:04:00.625 --> 00:04:01.461
Thank you.

00:04:01.531 --> 00:04:03.051
You should take it, Miki.

00:04:03.067 --> 00:04:04.297
You need it more than him.

00:04:04.906 --> 00:04:06.539
Now, which one of you is the doctor?

00:04:06.578 --> 00:04:09.148
At least someone cares about my hunger pains.

00:04:09.867 --> 00:04:10.551
Hey!

00:04:10.750 --> 00:04:12.258
Easy on the soy sauce.

00:04:12.672 --> 00:04:14.023
But I like it this way.

00:04:14.688 --> 00:04:16.453
Ooh, pass me the soy!

00:04:18.391 --> 00:04:20.454
Breakfast is ready, Sachiko!

00:04:20.695 --> 00:04:22.367
Yeah, I'll be right there.

00:04:22.756 --> 00:04:23.889
Good morning grandma.

00:04:24.904 --> 00:04:25.670
Good morning.

00:04:31.560 --> 00:04:34.919
Riku, why don't you and Umi share your mother's plate?

00:04:34.944 --> 00:04:35.608
Thank you.

00:04:36.251 --> 00:04:36.960
Grandmother.

00:04:36.985 --> 00:04:38.359
Would you like me to make you some tea?

00:04:38.836 --> 00:04:39.796
Yes, Umi.

00:04:39.796 --> 00:04:40.865
That would be lovely.

00:04:42.123 --> 00:04:43.420
Good morning, Sachiko.

00:04:43.905 --> 00:04:45.426
I bid you all good morning.

00:04:45.442 --> 00:04:46.256
Good morning.

00:04:49.978 --> 00:04:50.962
Thank you, dear.

00:04:57.188 --> 00:04:58.472
Please begin, everyone.

00:04:59.363 --> 00:05:00.809
I gratefully receive.

00:05:04.612 --> 00:05:05.324
You're late.

00:05:05.973 --> 00:05:07.902
I couldn't get my hair to look right.

00:05:09.209 --> 00:05:11.264
It looks like hair is supposed to look.

00:05:14.628 --> 00:05:15.769
I'm starving.

00:05:16.249 --> 00:05:17.902
Evening rounds again, Miki?

00:05:18.165 --> 00:05:18.684
Yes.

00:05:18.768 --> 00:05:20.214
I don't know how you keep up this pace.

00:05:20.230 --> 00:05:20.925
Can I have your dinner?

00:06:18.963 --> 00:06:20.247
See you tomorrow, Umi!

00:06:20.605 --> 00:06:21.327
Bye Miki!

00:06:45.840 --> 00:06:46.692
Good morning.

00:06:46.708 --> 00:06:47.655
Morning, Umi.

00:06:49.012 --> 00:06:50.325
Do you want a ride, Umi?

00:06:50.630 --> 00:06:51.511
No, thank you.

00:06:51.527 --> 00:06:51.902
I'll walk.

00:06:52.060 --> 00:06:53.153
Ah, to be young.

00:06:54.310 --> 00:06:56.146
Tomoko, could you finish the laundry for me?

00:06:56.395 --> 00:06:57.224
Of course.

00:06:57.240 --> 00:06:58.091
I'd be happy to.

00:06:58.450 --> 00:06:59.232
Thank you.

00:07:12.156 --> 00:07:13.080
Hey, wait up!

00:07:18.079 --> 00:07:18.579
Hi.

00:07:18.604 --> 00:07:19.246
Morning.

00:07:21.040 --> 00:07:22.041
You saw it already?

00:07:22.580 --> 00:07:23.720
Umi, over here!

00:07:23.736 --> 00:07:24.627
Come see this.

00:07:24.643 --> 00:07:25.307
What is it?

00:07:25.447 --> 00:07:27.244
Oh, just an article about you.

00:07:27.505 --> 00:07:28.846
It must be about you.

00:07:28.947 --> 00:07:30.721
Who else raises flags every morning?

00:07:31.759 --> 00:07:32.541
Fair girl.

00:07:32.697 --> 00:07:34.705
Why do you send your thoughts to the sky?

00:07:34.963 --> 00:07:37.705
The winds carries them aloft to mingle with the crows.

00:07:37.729 --> 00:07:40.830
Trimmed with blue, your flags fly again today.

00:07:40.846 --> 00:07:43.947
Aw, looks like someone's getting your messages.

00:07:44.313 --> 00:07:44.815
Mm-hm.

00:07:45.189 --> 00:07:45.979
I doubt it.

00:07:46.260 --> 00:07:50.111
Someone at this school getting
those messages just doesn't calculate.

00:07:50.136 --> 00:07:51.605
Math Club freak!

00:07:52.029 --> 00:07:55.713
He's one of those snobby guys that
lives at that dirty old club house.

00:07:58.369 --> 00:07:59.193
All rise!

00:08:01.498 --> 00:08:02.630
There you are.

00:08:02.646 --> 00:08:03.654
Sorry I'm late.

00:08:06.427 --> 00:08:07.279
I'm starving.

00:08:07.295 --> 00:08:08.130
Saved you a seat.

00:08:09.201 --> 00:08:11.396
Who ordered the curry noodles?

00:08:11.412 --> 00:08:12.795
So, what did he say?

00:08:13.091 --> 00:08:13.888
Nobuko!

00:08:14.239 --> 00:08:15.172
Over here.

00:08:16.037 --> 00:08:17.102
Thanks for waiting.

00:08:17.180 --> 00:08:18.437
Curry udon again?

00:08:18.966 --> 00:08:20.341
Oh, and you're one to talk.

00:08:20.475 --> 00:08:21.279
Let me guess.

00:08:21.334 --> 00:08:22.794
Tuna sandwiches again?

00:08:23.123 --> 00:08:23.853
Who cares?

00:08:23.878 --> 00:08:24.462
I like them.

00:08:24.966 --> 00:08:27.107
Umi, your lunches always look so good.

00:08:27.273 --> 00:08:28.498
It's not difficult.

00:08:28.691 --> 00:08:30.276
You should try making your own sometime.

00:08:30.301 --> 00:08:31.030
It'll never happen.

00:08:31.357 --> 00:08:32.349
I don't have the time.

00:08:34.229 --> 00:08:35.481
Hey!

00:08:36.934 --> 00:08:38.547
Great, now what?

00:08:51.151 --> 00:08:52.311
And up.

00:08:54.008 --> 00:08:57.261
One, two, one, two, one, two, one, two, one, two.

00:09:01.287 --> 00:09:01.869
Men!

00:09:02.038 --> 00:09:03.038
It's time.

00:09:04.154 --> 00:09:06.365
Save our building!

00:09:07.960 --> 00:09:08.911
OK, batter up.

00:09:46.923 --> 00:09:48.806
Smile for the camera, lovebirds!

00:09:48.822 --> 00:09:49.841
Give us a smile.

00:09:54.559 --> 00:09:56.004
That was so cool.

00:09:57.278 --> 00:09:58.536
Umi, are you OK?

00:09:59.615 --> 00:10:00.371
So stupid.

00:10:06.918 --> 00:10:07.894
I'm home!

00:10:08.499 --> 00:10:09.387
Welcome back.

00:10:09.785 --> 00:10:11.394
Oh, thank you Tomoko.

00:10:11.815 --> 00:10:12.676
My pleasure.

00:10:16.238 --> 00:10:16.871
There.

00:10:16.926 --> 00:10:17.683
All finished.

00:10:18.387 --> 00:10:20.066
The mackerel was on sale today.

00:10:20.551 --> 00:10:22.105
Mm, mackerel, that's good.

00:10:22.824 --> 00:10:23.738
Maybe I'll fry it.

00:10:24.320 --> 00:10:26.460
I almost forgot, I have a meeting with grandmother.

00:10:33.631 --> 00:10:34.241
Grandmother?

00:10:35.151 --> 00:10:36.116
It's me, Umi.

00:10:36.488 --> 00:10:37.256
Come in.

00:10:50.349 --> 00:10:51.545
Very impressive.

00:10:51.709 --> 00:10:53.553
You're managing the house beautifully.

00:10:54.810 --> 00:10:58.779
Only because you're paying to Tomoko's
wages, which is a tremendous help.

00:10:59.307 --> 00:11:00.271
Nonsense.

00:11:00.545 --> 00:11:04.303
I would have hired her anyway,
even if we hadn't taken in boarders.

00:11:05.139 --> 00:11:06.201
Tell me, my child.

00:11:06.474 --> 00:11:07.881
Is this too much work for you?

00:11:10.227 --> 00:11:11.381
I worry about you.

00:11:12.939 --> 00:11:13.474
But why?

00:11:13.490 --> 00:11:15.935
I promise I'm not letting it get in the way of my studies.

00:11:16.400 --> 00:11:16.889
Umi.

00:11:18.903 --> 00:11:22.842
Believe me, I know how much you miss your father.

00:11:23.199 --> 00:11:27.271
But it makes me sad watching you
every morning raising those flags.

00:11:28.329 --> 00:11:30.014
I hope you find someone.

00:11:30.247 --> 00:11:33.303
Then maybe you won't need to raise those flags anymore.

00:11:35.211 --> 00:11:36.334
I'm sorry to interrupt.

00:11:36.712 --> 00:11:37.394
Come in.

00:11:39.607 --> 00:11:41.256
I'm finished for the day, ma'am.

00:11:42.134 --> 00:11:43.045
Thank you, Tomoko.

00:11:46.081 --> 00:11:47.521
Excuse me, grandmother.

00:11:48.873 --> 00:11:49.896
I should get dinner going.

00:12:57.196 --> 00:12:58.485
It was very exciting.

00:12:58.891 --> 00:13:03.110
In fact, it created such a stir that some of
the girls are talking about starting a fan club.

00:13:03.379 --> 00:13:04.235
What?

00:13:04.251 --> 00:13:05.235
OK, so what's his name?

00:13:05.290 --> 00:13:08.219
Shun Kazama, and he is a real live wire.

00:13:08.258 --> 00:13:09.680
So he's the electrician's son?

00:13:10.172 --> 00:13:10.797
What?

00:13:38.640 --> 00:13:42.189
Fair girl, why do you send your thoughts to the sky?

00:13:57.962 --> 00:14:03.823
Thus the Principality of Wallachia was
hemmed in by the Ottoman Turks and Russia,

00:14:03.839 --> 00:14:06.576
and its territory was coveted by both.

00:14:19.734 --> 00:14:20.413
Hey Umi.

00:14:20.429 --> 00:14:21.914
Sora, what's going on?

00:14:24.601 --> 00:14:26.539
I bought this for 30 yen.

00:14:29.510 --> 00:14:31.484
Wow, that's a waste of money.

00:14:31.609 --> 00:14:32.859
I don't care what you say.

00:14:33.023 --> 00:14:35.141
I think he's cute, and I want to get his autograph.

00:14:35.166 --> 00:14:37.101
Please come with me to the Latin Quarter Clubhouse,

00:14:37.101 --> 00:14:39.617
so that way when I meet him, he doesn't think I'm weird.

00:14:39.633 --> 00:14:40.634
Are you crazy?

00:14:40.650 --> 00:14:42.054
I don't want to go to that old place.

00:14:42.070 --> 00:14:42.906
But I'm desperate.

00:14:42.922 --> 00:14:43.664
Well, I'm not.

00:14:44.656 --> 00:14:47.062
I know you're not, but you'll do it for me, won't you?

00:14:48.156 --> 00:14:49.172
Come on, say yes.

00:14:49.483 --> 00:14:49.765
Yes.

00:14:49.938 --> 00:14:50.396
Yes?

00:14:54.201 --> 00:14:54.601
Wow.

00:14:55.726 --> 00:14:58.069
They really like signs.

00:14:59.228 --> 00:15:00.979
Save the Latin Quarter.

00:15:02.585 --> 00:15:05.960
Don't extinguish the flame of culture?

00:15:08.827 --> 00:15:09.476
Ready?

00:15:09.842 --> 00:15:10.421
Mm-hm.

00:15:15.874 --> 00:15:17.366
Did you see those spots?

00:15:17.391 --> 00:15:18.212
Um, excuse me.

00:15:18.235 --> 00:15:18.696
Gentlemen?

00:15:19.118 --> 00:15:20.743
I've never seen them so distinct.

00:15:20.795 --> 00:15:23.329
This might be more awesome than the solar flares of 1960.

00:15:23.368 --> 00:15:24.954
Don't even joke about that.

00:15:25.016 --> 00:15:26.157
I said excuse me.

00:15:26.257 --> 00:15:27.370
What did you say?

00:15:27.568 --> 00:15:30.657
I'm sorry to interrupt, but we're
looking for the school newspaper office.

00:15:30.743 --> 00:15:33.290
Uh, third floor, same room as the Archeology Club.

00:15:33.727 --> 00:15:34.360
Thank you.

00:15:34.954 --> 00:15:35.994
What are girls doing here?

00:15:36.035 --> 00:15:36.938
I have no idea.

00:15:36.954 --> 00:15:37.774
Do you think they liked us?

00:15:51.800 --> 00:15:53.873
Well, I love what they've done with the place.

00:15:55.763 --> 00:15:56.537
Wait.

00:16:01.724 --> 00:16:02.364
Whoa.

00:16:15.014 --> 00:16:16.022
Ahoy.

00:16:16.450 --> 00:16:19.116
Excuse me, where's the Archaeology Club?

00:16:19.745 --> 00:16:20.596
Upstairs.

00:16:20.621 --> 00:16:23.015
Listen for the sounds of smug portentousness.

00:16:23.040 --> 00:16:24.022
OK, thank you.

00:16:24.413 --> 00:16:25.054
Ready?

00:16:25.155 --> 00:16:26.001
Mm-hm.

00:16:36.170 --> 00:16:37.650
Ah, at last.

00:16:37.846 --> 00:16:41.361
Inquiring minds seeking answers to life's great mysteries.

00:16:41.377 --> 00:16:41.830
Huh?

00:16:41.931 --> 00:16:48.564
I will personally offer you my stewardship and
share with you my passion for the philosophical arts.

00:16:48.580 --> 00:16:52.892
That's a very kind offer, but we're
actually headed for the. Archaeology Club.

00:16:53.028 --> 00:16:54.238
Fine, as you wish.

00:16:54.265 --> 00:16:56.833
But when you find yourself seeking the meaning of life,

00:16:57.408 --> 00:16:58.838
I'll be right here to enlighten you.

00:17:02.791 --> 00:17:05.713
Chemistry Club, you ruined our contemplation!

00:17:06.166 --> 00:17:06.667
Oh well.

00:17:06.692 --> 00:17:07.972
You're welcome, ladies.

00:17:08.144 --> 00:17:09.877
That guy'll talk your ear off.

00:17:09.908 --> 00:17:10.845
Hey, that's enough.

00:17:11.228 --> 00:17:13.525
Show some respect you second-rate alchemists.

00:17:13.541 --> 00:17:14.189
Here's a thought.

00:17:14.228 --> 00:17:17.476
Try experimenting with something that actually exists!

00:17:17.851 --> 00:17:22.421
Obtain new transparent energy from the
clouds, from the light, from the storms!

00:17:22.683 --> 00:17:26.046
And suggest to man and the
universe the shapes they are to take.

00:17:26.062 --> 00:17:29.694
Copernicus of the new age,
set this galaxy free from the...

00:17:30.181 --> 00:17:32.523
CQ, this is O-N-4-FMKK.

00:17:32.562 --> 00:17:33.093
Thanks, O-N.

00:17:33.140 --> 00:17:34.968
We are high school students from Japan!

00:17:51.299 --> 00:17:52.244
Watch your step.

00:17:53.139 --> 00:17:53.861
Mm-hm.

00:18:02.431 --> 00:18:02.927
That's it.

00:18:04.296 --> 00:18:04.850
Mm-hm.

00:18:06.852 --> 00:18:08.354
Oh, hi Umi.

00:18:08.354 --> 00:18:09.396
Yamazaki.

00:18:10.064 --> 00:18:12.818
Hey, couple of potential groupies here to see you.

00:18:13.233 --> 00:18:14.013
Ciao.

00:18:18.552 --> 00:18:20.138
Welcome to the Lit Club.

00:18:20.657 --> 00:18:22.302
Or Archeology Club.

00:18:22.747 --> 00:18:26.771
Or maybe you're the two who actually
read that failed weekly rag we publish.

00:18:26.826 --> 00:18:28.207
Knock it off, Mizunuma.

00:18:28.232 --> 00:18:30.647
Bring them in and close the door.

00:18:32.219 --> 00:18:36.395
The crux of the matter is, how
can we make archaeology cool again?

00:18:36.420 --> 00:18:37.092
We can't.

00:18:41.377 --> 00:18:42.322
Uh, uh.

00:18:42.846 --> 00:18:43.399
Oh.

00:18:45.307 --> 00:18:47.059
Can you please give me your autograph?

00:18:47.075 --> 00:18:47.487
Huh?

00:18:48.460 --> 00:18:49.909
Go ahead, Elvis.

00:18:50.396 --> 00:18:50.987
Hm.

00:19:00.214 --> 00:19:00.714
Here.

00:19:00.739 --> 00:19:01.240
Thank you.

00:19:01.265 --> 00:19:02.580
Thank you so much!

00:19:02.706 --> 00:19:03.578
How's your hand?

00:19:04.576 --> 00:19:04.993
This?

00:19:05.125 --> 00:19:06.396
This isn't from the fall.

00:19:06.421 --> 00:19:08.119
I cut myself shaving.

00:19:08.156 --> 00:19:09.337
He shaves.

00:19:09.832 --> 00:19:10.399
Shaving?

00:19:11.445 --> 00:19:14.904
Hey, how'd you like to help
Mr. Whiskers here cut some stencils?

00:19:15.000 --> 00:19:15.688
Huh?

00:19:16.156 --> 00:19:20.305
Because we're pretty busy with the campaign to
keep the Latin Quarter from getting demolished.

00:19:20.469 --> 00:19:21.664
You're the little sister, right?

00:19:21.937 --> 00:19:22.518
Yes.

00:19:22.636 --> 00:19:23.672
I'm Sora Matsuzaki.

00:19:24.328 --> 00:19:27.433
But if you need help with
stencils, Umi has better handwriting.

00:19:27.433 --> 00:19:28.058
Right, Umi?

00:19:28.058 --> 00:19:30.023
What are you talking about, Sora?

00:19:30.046 --> 00:19:30.767
I don't have time...

00:19:30.791 --> 00:19:35.955
Look, if you're a second year student, you
take physics, and your teacher is old man Suzuki.

00:19:37.651 --> 00:19:38.650
Mr. Suzuki.

00:19:39.027 --> 00:19:44.814
Right, well, Mizunuma uses these old tests to
make up a mock test for the upcoming physics exam.

00:19:44.830 --> 00:19:45.650
That's right.

00:19:45.986 --> 00:19:48.775
But it's not really cheating
if they're only half accurate.

00:19:51.072 --> 00:19:52.564
Shun, see you at 6:007?

00:19:52.696 --> 00:19:53.431
Right.

00:19:53.517 --> 00:19:55.455
Miss Sora, please come with me.

00:19:56.036 --> 00:19:56.681
OK.

00:20:00.841 --> 00:20:06.658
With your permission, I will escort you to the
door, lest you be ambushed by our resident philosopher.

00:20:07.206 --> 00:20:08.348
Permission granted.

00:20:13.937 --> 00:20:15.485
Hm.

00:20:20.099 --> 00:20:20.478
Hm?

00:20:27.951 --> 00:20:29.413
From here to the end.

00:20:29.429 --> 00:20:29.866
Mm-hm.

00:20:43.639 --> 00:20:45.288
And I say we are cool.

00:20:45.537 --> 00:20:49.225
We have to get people interested
in the Paleolithic Period.

00:20:49.249 --> 00:20:50.428
To the library!

00:21:34.129 --> 00:21:35.245
Meeting's starting, Shun.

00:21:35.769 --> 00:21:37.489
Oh, you might wanna join us, Umi.

00:21:37.777 --> 00:21:40.128
If you like a room full of guys screaming at each other.

00:21:40.433 --> 00:21:41.441
Is it that late?

00:21:41.996 --> 00:21:42.401
I'm sorry.

00:21:42.401 --> 00:21:43.214
I have to go.

00:21:43.472 --> 00:21:44.269
It's OK.

00:21:44.653 --> 00:21:45.542
You were a big help.

00:21:47.197 --> 00:21:48.583
Meeting time!

00:21:48.907 --> 00:21:52.286
All club members to the first floor!

00:21:52.313 --> 00:21:54.579
Meeting time!

00:21:56.951 --> 00:21:58.359
Check it out, X chromosome.

00:22:18.385 --> 00:22:19.180
I'm home!

00:22:48.176 --> 00:22:49.613
Wow, starting kind of late.

00:22:49.675 --> 00:22:50.718
Yes, I know.

00:22:50.844 --> 00:22:52.512
And I still need to cut some vegetables.

00:22:52.537 --> 00:22:53.357
Can you help me out?

00:22:53.544 --> 00:22:54.608
I hope so.

00:23:13.066 --> 00:23:14.635
Grandmother, I'm home.

00:23:14.660 --> 00:23:16.021
You're running a bit late, Umi.

00:23:16.037 --> 00:23:19.724
Riku, we're all out of pork, and I need you
to run down to the butcher shop and get some.

00:23:19.940 --> 00:23:22.334
Uh, no?

00:23:23.293 --> 00:23:23.888
Sora”?

00:23:24.373 --> 00:23:27.560
But the program just started and this is my favorite part.

00:23:28.298 --> 00:23:29.935
But didn't Tomoko buy you some?

00:23:31.051 --> 00:23:32.543
I used it all for the lunches.

00:23:39.001 --> 00:23:41.577
Sachiko, start the rice in ten minutes, OK?

00:23:41.705 --> 00:23:45.190
Rice, and chopping, and rice.

00:23:58.560 --> 00:23:59.487
Going shopping?

00:23:59.996 --> 00:24:00.659
Sort of.

00:24:03.065 --> 00:24:03.674
Hop on.

00:24:03.690 --> 00:24:05.416
I'll give you a ride to the bottom of the hill.

00:24:06.213 --> 00:24:07.573
Ah, don't worry about this.

00:24:07.838 --> 00:24:09.487
I can break just fine with three fingers.

00:24:09.923 --> 00:24:10.627
What do you say?

00:24:25.960 --> 00:24:27.749
I thought you were at your meeting.

00:24:28.108 --> 00:24:29.858
Yeah, I was, but I left.

00:24:30.527 --> 00:24:32.764
I've got to get back home before my curfew.

00:24:35.202 --> 00:24:37.617
Did you finish printing the midterm mock test?

00:24:37.642 --> 00:24:38.977
Not even close.

00:24:39.161 --> 00:24:41.788
I'll get in early tomorrow and do it before school starts.

00:24:45.678 --> 00:24:48.007
Shun, do you mind if I ask you a question?

00:24:48.587 --> 00:24:49.069
Hm?

00:24:50.547 --> 00:24:52.466
About the poem in the pa...

00:24:52.833 --> 00:24:53.562
Hang on!

00:25:00.714 --> 00:25:01.402
You were saying?

00:25:02.159 --> 00:25:03.901
Hm, nothing.

00:25:16.573 --> 00:25:17.335
Thank you, Shun.

00:25:19.577 --> 00:25:20.452
Hi Mr. Ishii.

00:25:20.476 --> 00:25:22.046
I need some sliced pork, please.

00:25:22.468 --> 00:25:23.280
Hi Umi.

00:25:23.439 --> 00:25:24.538
Two to go, please.

00:25:25.123 --> 00:25:27.374
Because it's for you, there's a little extra.

00:25:27.390 --> 00:25:28.312
You're very kind.

00:25:31.097 --> 00:25:31.853
Here you are.

00:25:31.880 --> 00:25:32.773
Have a good evening.

00:25:33.616 --> 00:25:34.444
Next in line.

00:25:34.841 --> 00:25:35.499
Thanks for waiting.

00:25:36.187 --> 00:25:36.836
Mm.

00:25:36.852 --> 00:25:37.609
Have one.

00:25:40.706 --> 00:25:42.382
Won't make it on an empty stomach.

00:25:43.484 --> 00:25:44.530
Where do you live?

00:25:45.305 --> 00:25:45.889
Downtown.

00:25:45.936 --> 00:25:46.311
Oh.

00:25:46.530 --> 00:25:47.687
That's pretty far.

00:25:47.703 --> 00:25:48.359
Mm-hm.

00:25:51.149 --> 00:25:52.057
Gotta go.

00:25:54.157 --> 00:25:55.314
Thanks for the ride.

00:25:55.748 --> 00:25:56.549
You're welcome!

00:26:06.823 --> 00:26:08.111
This is nice.

00:26:28.929 --> 00:26:31.424
Sachiko, can I come in?

00:26:33.565 --> 00:26:34.830
Are you not feeling well?

00:26:39.666 --> 00:26:41.283
You'd better go ahead without me.

00:26:42.174 --> 00:26:43.268
Wake up, Sachiko.

00:26:56.282 --> 00:26:56.770
Whoa.

00:26:57.460 --> 00:26:58.452
I know.

00:27:07.612 --> 00:27:08.318
Ugh.

00:27:09.018 --> 00:27:11.112
The colors are wrong when I paint at night.

00:27:12.307 --> 00:27:13.270
It's beautiful.

00:27:15.323 --> 00:27:16.268
What's this?

00:27:17.311 --> 00:27:20.041
That's a boat I often see passing by.

00:27:20.657 --> 00:27:24.463
This might sound crazy, but I
think it's answering your flags.

00:27:25.327 --> 00:27:26.268
Oh, yeah.

00:27:26.507 --> 00:27:28.106
You can't see it from the garden.

00:27:30.206 --> 00:27:32.229
Answering my flags?

00:27:40.733 --> 00:27:41.764
What day is it?

00:28:03.873 --> 00:28:04.624
Good morning.

00:28:04.658 --> 00:28:05.347
Morning, Shun.

00:28:05.363 --> 00:28:06.152
Did you finish?

00:28:06.313 --> 00:28:07.371
All printed up.

00:28:07.387 --> 00:28:08.746
Would you like to see your handiwork?

00:28:09.722 --> 00:28:10.582
Look at that.

00:28:12.332 --> 00:28:13.488
Shun, I, uh...

00:28:18.546 --> 00:28:21.136
There was something printed in
the paper I wanted to ask you about.

00:28:21.591 --> 00:28:22.277
OK.

00:28:23.910 --> 00:28:25.800
Um, now might not be the best time.

00:28:25.816 --> 00:28:27.410
Maybe just after school?

00:28:27.597 --> 00:28:31.925
Yeah, I was going to ask you to do some more
stencils, so maybe we can meet at the clubhouse?

00:28:31.997 --> 00:28:32.800
That works.

00:28:33.620 --> 00:28:36.539
It will have to be tomorrow, though,
because there's a big debate today.

00:28:36.564 --> 00:28:37.273
Do you want to come?

00:28:37.273 --> 00:28:40.019
I'd love to, but I have too much I have to get done.

00:28:41.194 --> 00:28:41.736
Oh!

00:28:42.089 --> 00:28:42.871
But I'll try.

00:28:42.988 --> 00:28:43.777
Sure, OK.

00:28:50.396 --> 00:28:51.403
Umi, wait up!

00:28:51.745 --> 00:28:53.014
You want to get some ice cream?

00:28:53.039 --> 00:28:54.551
I thought you had practice.

00:28:54.567 --> 00:28:57.051
It was canceled because of that stupid debate.

00:28:57.489 --> 00:28:58.293
I can't go to.

00:28:58.406 --> 00:29:00.840
Tomoko's off today, and I really should get home early.

00:29:01.629 --> 00:29:05.082
This way for the historic debate,
future of the Latin Quarter to be decided!

00:29:08.780 --> 00:29:09.739
All right, good!

00:29:09.764 --> 00:29:10.462
Stop there.

00:29:13.643 --> 00:29:14.894
This is going to get rough.

00:29:19.678 --> 00:29:20.242
Umi.

00:29:20.970 --> 00:29:21.776
You heading home?

00:29:21.955 --> 00:29:23.564
Because I got some really nice flounder.

00:29:23.878 --> 00:29:24.838
Um, sure.

00:29:24.863 --> 00:29:25.655
I'll take some.

00:29:25.680 --> 00:29:26.495
Coming right up.

00:29:27.125 --> 00:29:28.622
Hey, is your mom back from America?

00:29:29.017 --> 00:29:29.759
Not yet.

00:29:30.618 --> 00:29:32.245
I'll, uh, come back for the fish later.

00:29:32.270 --> 00:29:33.690
Wha... how much later?

00:29:38.836 --> 00:29:42.344
Construct a new state of the
art student center in its place!

00:29:42.689 --> 00:29:45.191
Japan is a nation in transition!

00:29:45.216 --> 00:29:49.179
We have suffered the scars of war,
and we have emerged a stronger people!

00:29:49.204 --> 00:29:50.655
A peaceful people!

00:29:50.680 --> 00:29:52.182
A modern people!

00:29:56.436 --> 00:29:59.814
We cannot stand in the way of progress.

00:29:59.830 --> 00:30:04.687
The Tokyo Olympics will showcase our new
democracy as a bright beacon to guide the world...

00:30:04.703 --> 00:30:05.577
Oh, Umi.

00:30:05.593 --> 00:30:06.039
...into a promising new future!

00:30:06.055 --> 00:30:07.351
What are they yelling about?

00:30:07.694 --> 00:30:08.577
I have no idea.

00:30:08.593 --> 00:30:11.359
But how can we lead into the
future if we still cling to the past?

00:30:11.398 --> 00:30:16.020
It is time we throw these old
buildings out as relics of a bygone era!

00:30:16.101 --> 00:30:21.695
Our polls say 80% of you want the Latin Quarter torn down!

00:30:26.132 --> 00:30:28.651
Your ideas of democracy make me laugh.

00:30:28.760 --> 00:30:31.805
We've come here to debate; you've
already made up our minds for us.

00:30:31.830 --> 00:30:34.157
Sit back down, or I'll have you thrown out!

00:30:34.182 --> 00:30:36.851
You're just like the old men who run this country!

00:30:36.938 --> 00:30:39.102
Dumb and enamored with the new!

00:30:40.547 --> 00:30:41.831
I'm sick of that building!

00:30:41.847 --> 00:30:43.143
It's time to tear it down!

00:30:43.197 --> 00:30:44.657
It's about the Olympics!

00:30:45.026 --> 00:30:45.713
Yeah!

00:30:45.893 --> 00:30:46.954
Let him speak!

00:30:56.294 --> 00:30:56.896
Listen!

00:30:57.163 --> 00:31:00.255
If you're so hell-bent on demolition,
demolish your shortsighted thinking!

00:31:00.271 --> 00:31:01.042
That's enough!

00:31:01.042 --> 00:31:01.793
Sit down!

00:31:01.793 --> 00:31:05.864
You cannot move into the future
without first knowing the past!

00:31:05.948 --> 00:31:10.325
Destroy everything old and you dishonor
those who lived and died before us.

00:31:10.552 --> 00:31:14.216
The Olympics has the whole country
thinking all that glitters is gold.

00:31:14.536 --> 00:31:15.707
Well, I say it's not!

00:31:15.849 --> 00:31:20.186
And just because the majority disagrees,
doesn't mean we're going down without a fight!

00:31:20.211 --> 00:31:21.366
Anarchists!

00:31:21.521 --> 00:31:22.286
Charge!

00:31:23.747 --> 00:31:24.966
<i>Here they come!</i>

00:31:25.984 --> 00:31:26.794
Stand!

00:31:26.985 --> 00:31:28.989
Stand fast, men!

00:31:30.488 --> 00:31:31.419
We're not history!

00:31:31.435 --> 00:31:32.560
You're history!

00:31:36.923 --> 00:31:38.399
Very graceful!

00:31:39.040 --> 00:31:40.704
You should start attacking!

00:31:54.220 --> 00:31:58.875
I still remember that day long ago.

00:31:59.559 --> 00:32:06.454
You looked away, but I saw you crying for me.

00:32:07.258 --> 00:32:12.488
Sayonara, you said, my love.

00:32:13.011 --> 00:32:22.222
When morning came, you left an
ivory flower, my lone memory of you.

00:32:23.416 --> 00:32:33.863
I walk alone, still hoping to find you,
the flower that blooms inside of my heart.

00:32:34.260 --> 00:32:44.720
I walk alone, still hoping to find you,
the flower that blooms inside of my heart.

00:32:49.150 --> 00:32:49.723
Umi!

00:32:50.235 --> 00:32:51.285
So what did you think?

00:32:51.819 --> 00:32:53.457
I think it was amazing.

00:32:53.680 --> 00:32:55.028
You're all so passionate.

00:32:55.442 --> 00:32:57.408
Yeah, debates are always like that.

00:32:57.433 --> 00:33:00.264
I hate that everyone thinks
the clubhouse is just an eyesore.

00:33:00.340 --> 00:33:02.207
They don't care what's going on inside.

00:33:02.830 --> 00:33:03.895
You really think so?

00:33:17.409 --> 00:33:18.339
Hey, I know.

00:33:18.471 --> 00:33:20.277
Why don't you all just clean the place up?

00:33:20.473 --> 00:33:21.081
Huh?

00:33:21.683 --> 00:33:24.560
It's a great old building, but
no one can see it through the dust.

00:33:24.585 --> 00:33:25.294
So clean it up.

00:33:25.378 --> 00:33:26.646
Make it look like new again.

00:33:26.671 --> 00:33:27.473
Make it cool.

00:33:27.636 --> 00:33:29.050
Maybe invite a few girls.

00:33:29.933 --> 00:33:31.308
Then the boys will like it, too.

00:33:31.480 --> 00:33:32.777
You're probably right.

00:33:33.214 --> 00:33:36.933
I would just have to convince everyone the
dust isn't an important part of its history.

00:33:37.240 --> 00:33:39.972
The physics midterm mock test was a huge success.

00:33:40.238 --> 00:33:42.909
I think it won you guys more than a few admirers.

00:33:43.417 --> 00:33:44.448
Me included.

00:33:50.072 --> 00:33:50.705
OK.

00:33:50.884 --> 00:33:53.767
Well, um, here are the stencils.

00:33:54.007 --> 00:33:54.775
Thanks again.

00:33:56.182 --> 00:33:56.892
Bye, Shun.

00:33:57.077 --> 00:33:57.845
Bye, Umi.

00:34:02.767 --> 00:34:04.293
And thanks for the advice!

00:34:15.465 --> 00:34:16.620
Forgot about the fish.

00:34:18.660 --> 00:34:22.090
It was such a big fight, and they
were going to be in so much trouble.

00:34:22.106 --> 00:34:26.086
But Mizunuma got them all to start
singing, and the teachers were totally fooled!

00:34:30.293 --> 00:34:31.895
Sounds like nothing's changed.

00:34:32.337 --> 00:34:34.567
When I was there, that stuff happened all the time.

00:34:34.881 --> 00:34:38.176
Your president, Mizunuma, is the
little brother of a classmate of mine.

00:34:38.192 --> 00:34:38.801
Really?

00:34:39.130 --> 00:34:41.204
Was his brother also a genius?

00:34:41.419 --> 00:34:42.481
His sister.

00:34:42.789 --> 00:34:44.395
She's an astrophysicist.

00:34:44.572 --> 00:34:45.406
Wow!

00:34:45.516 --> 00:34:46.841
Here you go, doctor.

00:34:47.112 --> 00:34:48.453
From my secret stash.

00:34:48.478 --> 00:34:49.645
Is that whiskey?

00:34:49.670 --> 00:34:51.725
As a matter of fact, it is.

00:34:51.794 --> 00:34:52.887
Oh, glasses.

00:34:52.903 --> 00:34:53.669
Can I have some?

00:34:53.685 --> 00:34:54.817
Sora, you're too young.

00:34:55.385 --> 00:34:56.303
Hey.

00:34:56.319 --> 00:34:59.794
How about we invite some of the guys
from school to my going away party?

00:35:00.265 --> 00:35:02.309
What guys?

00:35:02.570 --> 00:35:04.598
The really cute ones.

00:35:06.662 --> 00:35:07.914
Really cute what?

00:35:29.561 --> 00:35:30.237
Hey, Umi.

00:35:33.981 --> 00:35:38.101
H-O-K-U-T. Hokuto.

00:35:38.430 --> 00:35:40.794
Hey, I didn't know you could read signal flags.

00:35:46.853 --> 00:35:47.966
Thank you both for coming.

00:35:48.415 --> 00:35:49.375
Umi, we're ready.

00:35:49.414 --> 00:35:50.481
OK!

00:36:02.395 --> 00:36:07.465
Forgive my sense of tradition, but why not
get married and start a practice right here?

00:36:07.791 --> 00:36:09.489
Would that mean we'd all have to move out?

00:36:09.566 --> 00:36:11.614
You'll probably be married by then.

00:36:11.793 --> 00:36:13.463
Oh, if only that were true.

00:36:13.479 --> 00:36:16.176
I'm going to marry a man who's brilliant, but sensitive.

00:36:16.493 --> 00:36:17.653
Hm, is he here?

00:36:18.151 --> 00:36:19.684
The trustees are the problem.

00:36:20.002 --> 00:36:22.130
We can't let them tear the place down.

00:36:22.155 --> 00:36:22.738
Agreed.

00:36:22.763 --> 00:36:23.795
What can we do?

00:36:24.073 --> 00:36:25.533
We need to go over their heads.

00:36:25.829 --> 00:36:26.485
To who?

00:36:26.617 --> 00:36:28.494
The principal just does what the board tells him.

00:36:28.809 --> 00:36:29.504
I don't know.

00:36:29.910 --> 00:36:32.355
We all just need to be really smart about this.

00:36:32.371 --> 00:36:33.285
We need a strategy.

00:36:33.629 --> 00:36:35.653
We need one fast, before it's too late.

00:36:39.597 --> 00:36:41.284
We keep running out of glasses.

00:36:41.591 --> 00:36:42.432
Well, I'll wash some.

00:36:42.984 --> 00:36:44.068
You take that out.

00:36:44.093 --> 00:36:44.737
OK.

00:36:48.852 --> 00:36:49.709
OK, everyone.

00:36:49.725 --> 00:36:50.724
Sushi's ready.

00:36:53.209 --> 00:36:55.420
This building was built at the turn of the century.

00:36:55.630 --> 00:36:56.998
It actually used to be a hospital.

00:37:04.629 --> 00:37:05.850
See that carving up there?

00:37:06.355 --> 00:37:07.800
It's over a hundred years old.

00:37:08.206 --> 00:37:09.933
My great-grandfather loved cats.

00:37:10.878 --> 00:37:14.011
Compared to the clubhouse, this
all looks practically brand new.

00:37:14.306 --> 00:37:15.300
It's incredible.

00:37:15.948 --> 00:37:18.300
And I'm guessing you're part of the reason why?

00:37:19.816 --> 00:37:21.581
So your grandfather was a doctor?

00:37:22.128 --> 00:37:23.433
Was your dad a doctor, too?

00:37:23.598 --> 00:37:24.323
Mm-mm.

00:37:24.683 --> 00:37:26.058
He was the captain of a ship.

00:37:29.375 --> 00:37:33.760
From this valley they say you are going.

00:37:34.302 --> 00:37:38.565
We will miss your bright eyes, and your smile.

00:37:39.057 --> 00:37:42.049
Far from us, you are taking the sunshine...

00:37:42.065 --> 00:37:44.236
So your mom married a sailor.

00:37:44.643 --> 00:37:49.706
My grandpa and gran, they didn't approve of the
marriage, and so they tried to stop it from happening.

00:37:50.307 --> 00:37:53.760
But my mom wouldn't let anything
stand in the way of true love.

00:37:53.841 --> 00:37:55.259
That took guts.

00:37:55.588 --> 00:37:57.752
She defied her parents and married him anyway?

00:37:58.427 --> 00:37:59.057
Mm-hm.

00:38:00.182 --> 00:38:03.230
And your dad, he taught you how to use the signal flags.

00:38:08.926 --> 00:38:09.897
Mm, yeah, he did.

00:38:10.155 --> 00:38:11.406
When I was just a girl.

00:38:16.349 --> 00:38:21.029
He said they helped him find his way
back to us, so I raised them every day.

00:38:22.465 --> 00:38:23.674
It was at our old house.

00:38:25.091 --> 00:38:27.646
I'd raise them from the balcony
until his ship docked again.

00:38:29.127 --> 00:38:29.732
Every day.

00:38:31.445 --> 00:38:33.115
Every single day.

00:38:35.898 --> 00:38:37.867
Then we got news about his ship.

00:38:38.266 --> 00:38:40.149
That it sank during the Korean War.

00:38:41.680 --> 00:38:43.742
They never found him, and that was that.

00:38:45.047 --> 00:38:48.297
But I kept raising the flags,
hoping they might help him find me.

00:38:48.930 --> 00:38:52.188
And when we moved here, I was
so upset, I couldn't stop crying.

00:38:52.497 --> 00:38:55.524
There was nowhere to raise the flags, and I felt so lost.

00:38:56.428 --> 00:38:58.240
So grandpa built me that flagpole.

00:39:13.929 --> 00:39:15.180
We could use a little light.

00:39:18.477 --> 00:39:21.173
Grandmother said this used to be my grandfather's office,

00:39:21.438 --> 00:39:23.665
but now it's sort of become my mom's private study.

00:39:23.806 --> 00:39:25.220
She sure likes to read.

00:39:27.314 --> 00:39:28.736
Is this your family?

00:39:29.720 --> 00:39:30.267
Yes.

00:39:31.530 --> 00:39:32.298
Your father?

00:39:34.132 --> 00:39:34.757
Mm-mm.

00:39:35.183 --> 00:39:36.457
That's my grandfather.

