01:04:13.529 --> 01:04:14.294
Thanks for waiting.

01:04:14.567 --> 01:04:15.109
You're welcome.

01:04:15.134 --> 01:04:15.343
No problem.

01:04:16.068 --> 01:04:17.568
We're very happy you're coming with us.

01:04:17.699 --> 01:04:18.207
Me too.

01:04:18.232 --> 01:04:20.373
It'll help take my mind off other things.

01:04:20.531 --> 01:04:21.323
Ticket, ma'am?

01:04:21.323 --> 01:04:22.849
Yes OK.

01:04:23.159 --> 01:04:23.802
Let's go.

01:05:10.015 --> 01:05:11.165
Well, into the breach?

01:05:11.190 --> 01:05:11.565
Mm-hm.

01:05:13.080 --> 01:05:14.721
Students from the Konan Academy.

01:05:15.338 --> 01:05:16.002
That's right.

01:05:17.549 --> 01:05:19.215
And you don't have an appointment?

01:05:19.215 --> 01:05:19.744
No, sir.

01:05:19.760 --> 01:05:21.776
We're appealing directly to Mr. Tokumaru.

01:05:22.260 --> 01:05:24.291
Something about a direct appeal.

01:05:24.916 --> 01:05:25.471
No.

01:05:25.705 --> 01:05:27.408
No, they don't seem like radicals.

01:05:28.349 --> 01:05:29.424
There's three of them.

01:05:30.935 --> 01:05:31.393
Al right.

01:05:31.393 --> 01:05:32.182
I'll tell them.

01:05:33.588 --> 01:05:38.182
Take the elevator at the end of the hall to the
fourth floor, and his office will be on the right.

01:05:38.651 --> 01:05:40.018
Thank you very much for your help.

01:05:40.268 --> 01:05:41.283
Don't forget to sign in.

01:05:41.487 --> 01:05:43.323
And next time, make an appointment.

01:05:51.506 --> 01:05:53.210
It's hard to know what's going to happen.

01:05:53.410 --> 01:05:55.139
Are you those students from Konan?

01:05:55.668 --> 01:05:56.147
Ma'am.

01:05:57.836 --> 01:06:03.499
Mr. Tokumaru is a very busy man, and he doesn't
normally see people who haven't made an appointment.

01:06:03.905 --> 01:06:04.510
Yes, ma'am.

01:06:04.510 --> 01:06:05.249
We understand.

01:06:05.397 --> 01:06:09.491
But speaking frankly, ma'am, we didn't actually believe
we would get an appointment if we called to make one.

01:06:09.958 --> 01:06:10.350
Ma'am.

01:06:11.108 --> 01:06:12.842
You're probably wasting your time.

01:06:12.977 --> 01:06:17.616
But since you seem determined, you can wait on
the bench as long as you don't disturb anyone.

01:06:18.530 --> 01:06:20.085
We thank you for your time, ma'am!

01:06:21.026 --> 01:06:22.361
What a year Nagashima's having.

01:06:22.361 --> 01:06:24.029
He could win another MVP.

01:06:24.029 --> 01:06:25.364
Scoring a lot of goals.

01:06:25.364 --> 01:06:25.864
Goals?

01:06:25.864 --> 01:06:27.288
Have you even seen baseball?

01:06:35.207 --> 01:06:36.024
Thank you, ma'am.

01:06:56.228 --> 01:06:56.882
Oh!

01:07:02.725 --> 01:07:03.733
Come on, then.

01:07:03.863 --> 01:07:04.828
Let's go get a drink.

01:07:04.862 --> 01:07:06.217
Quick, before he makes us stay.

01:07:19.626 --> 01:07:20.556
You're still here?

01:07:20.695 --> 01:07:21.767
Well, come on in.

01:07:22.522 --> 01:07:23.337
Thank you.

01:07:26.041 --> 01:07:27.048
Oh, yes. Right.

01:07:27.064 --> 01:07:28.072
Thank you for seeing us.

01:07:28.877 --> 01:07:29.806
Uh-huh.

01:07:30.697 --> 01:07:31.455
Yes?

01:07:31.767 --> 01:07:32.517
Uh-huh.

01:07:33.173 --> 01:07:34.080
Hang on.

01:07:34.314 --> 01:07:35.064
Have a seat.

01:07:35.447 --> 01:07:37.056
I'll be with you gentlemen in a minute.

01:07:37.986 --> 01:07:38.896
Al right.

01:07:38.896 --> 01:07:40.423
I've made my decision.

01:07:40.541 --> 01:07:42.634
I can't agree to that right now.

01:07:43.228 --> 01:07:43.884
Yes.

01:07:44.193 --> 01:07:44.759
Bye.

01:07:50.936 --> 01:07:51.926
Sit down.

01:07:52.418 --> 01:07:54.878
Why are you kids here today, and not in school?

01:07:55.184 --> 01:07:56.816
Because, sir, we escaped.

01:07:57.706 --> 01:07:58.660
Escaped, huh?

01:07:58.676 --> 01:08:00.254
I did that a lot myself.

01:08:00.521 --> 01:08:01.012
Yeah.

01:08:01.835 --> 01:08:04.588
Well, I guess you're here to
talk to me about that old clubhouse.

01:08:04.588 --> 01:08:05.074
Yes.

01:08:05.325 --> 01:08:08.092
We've come to you directly to ask
you to see the building for yourself.

01:08:08.285 --> 01:08:09.746
We've put a lot of work into it.

01:08:09.761 --> 01:08:10.816
Come see what we've done.

01:08:10.832 --> 01:08:11.926
That's all we're asking.

01:08:11.942 --> 01:08:12.793
Hm.

01:08:13.770 --> 01:08:15.113
What year are you, young lady?

01:08:15.690 --> 01:08:16.481
Second year.

01:08:16.725 --> 01:08:18.566
My name is Umi Matsuzaki.

01:08:18.685 --> 01:08:20.934
Sir, that building is more than just a building.

01:08:22.692 --> 01:08:25.192
And tell me, how is it more than just a building?

01:08:25.395 --> 01:08:27.786
Oh, because we all love it.

01:08:27.802 --> 01:08:30.481
And it makes us feel connected to our past.

01:08:30.864 --> 01:08:32.247
Like we belong to something.

01:08:34.664 --> 01:08:36.743
Connected to our past.

01:08:36.931 --> 01:08:37.688
Hm.

01:08:38.212 --> 01:08:39.884
May I ask what your father did?

01:08:41.204 --> 01:08:43.766
He was a captain on a supply ship.

01:08:44.192 --> 01:08:46.360
But his ship sank during the Korean War.

01:08:51.874 --> 01:08:53.760
They had made a delivery and were coming home.

01:08:56.330 --> 01:08:57.533
But his ship hit a mine.

01:09:19.949 --> 01:09:21.105
A supply ship.

01:09:21.693 --> 01:09:22.238
Yes, sir.

01:09:24.187 --> 01:09:25.113
I'm sorry.

01:09:26.352 --> 01:09:30.058
I know it must have been very hard
for your mother, raising you on her own.

01:09:30.824 --> 01:09:32.777
She obviously did a fine job.

01:09:34.148 --> 01:09:34.879
Thank you.

01:09:36.799 --> 01:09:37.683
All right.

01:09:37.803 --> 01:09:38.668
I'll go.

01:09:42.475 --> 01:09:43.816
Thank you, Mr. Chairman!

01:09:46.460 --> 01:09:47.749
So, tomorrow.

01:09:48.228 --> 01:09:49.045
How's it look?

01:09:50.678 --> 01:09:52.108
Right, that's in the evening.

01:09:53.772 --> 01:09:55.030
Move the rest to Friday.

01:09:57.208 --> 01:09:59.701
Now, I'll be there tomorrow afternoon.

01:09:59.799 --> 01:10:01.670
I'll handle everything with your principal.

01:10:01.778 --> 01:10:03.397
The rest will be your job.

01:10:05.510 --> 01:10:06.385
I know, I know.

01:10:09.010 --> 01:10:10.506
I actually didn't think that would work.

01:10:10.713 --> 01:10:12.260
Yeah, I'm still not sure it has.

01:10:14.090 --> 01:10:15.424
Well, I'm glad we came.

01:10:18.048 --> 01:10:20.244
I promised my mom I'd go visit my uncle.

01:10:20.525 --> 01:10:21.433
See you tomorrow!

01:10:58.595 --> 01:10:59.562
What do you think you'll do?

01:10:59.578 --> 01:11:01.163
You know, after graduation?

01:11:01.663 --> 01:11:02.307
Hm.

01:11:02.307 --> 01:11:05.335
Well, we don't have much money,
so probably National University.

01:11:05.932 --> 01:11:07.234
What'll happen to the Weekly?

01:11:08.359 --> 01:11:11.249
I'll have to find somebody
dedicated enough to take it over.

01:11:11.946 --> 01:11:12.798
What about you?

01:11:14.782 --> 01:11:19.609
I haven't decided, but I'm sort of
thinking I might like to be a doctor.

01:11:19.992 --> 01:11:20.351
Hm.

01:11:28.090 --> 01:11:29.133
Shun, are you...

01:11:29.360 --> 01:11:31.528
Are you one who wrote that poem in the paper?

01:11:31.711 --> 01:11:32.333
Mm-hm.

01:11:32.989 --> 01:11:36.942
I saw those flags every morning from my
dad's tugboat, and I found out it was you.

01:11:38.427 --> 01:11:41.348
Well, I can't really see any of the boats from the garden.

01:11:42.076 --> 01:11:46.380
So that's why I never noticed there
was somebody out there, answering me.

01:11:58.560 --> 01:11:59.478
Can I tell you something?

01:11:59.606 --> 01:12:00.085
Hm?

01:12:02.428 --> 01:12:04.740
Those flags that I raise.

01:12:07.213 --> 01:12:11.126
They're a message to my father, and
it says, I pray for your safe return.

01:12:11.269 --> 01:12:15.464
But he knows he can never come back to me,
so what I think he did was send you instead.

01:12:20.382 --> 01:12:22.842
And I don't really know what to do, because we're...

01:12:22.858 --> 01:12:23.481
Umi.

01:12:24.052 --> 01:12:28.481
Look, I know we can't do anything
about it, but just know, I love you.

01:12:38.740 --> 01:12:40.302
And I love you, too.

01:13:00.911 --> 01:13:01.968
Hey, I'm home.

01:13:08.888 --> 01:13:09.913
Mom, you're home.

01:13:10.827 --> 01:13:13.061
Umi, it's good to be back.

01:13:14.040 --> 01:13:15.955
Tell me about America and your studies.

01:13:16.021 --> 01:13:18.486
Oh, I learned something new every day.

01:13:19.486 --> 01:13:21.655
But mostly how much I missed home.

01:13:21.655 --> 01:13:23.027
And we missed you.

01:13:23.126 --> 01:13:25.298
This is the best thing I've ever ate.

01:13:25.790 --> 01:13:27.353
It's beef jerky.

01:13:27.828 --> 01:13:28.736
So is it pork?

01:13:29.121 --> 01:13:31.456
Sachiko, beef means cow.

01:13:44.554 --> 01:13:45.078
Mom?

01:13:47.723 --> 01:13:48.515
What's wrong?

01:13:48.540 --> 01:13:49.580
Why are you awake?

01:13:54.173 --> 01:13:56.273
There's something I need to talk to you about.

01:13:56.523 --> 01:13:57.586
Of course, Umi.

01:14:03.532 --> 01:14:05.152
It must be the time change.

01:14:05.536 --> 01:14:09.003
I can't sleep, so I thought I would
organize these books I got in America.

01:14:09.098 --> 01:14:10.411
There's this boy at school.

01:14:10.570 --> 01:14:12.535
His name is Shun Kazama.

01:14:15.966 --> 01:14:20.464
I'm so confused, because he came here for Miki's
party, and I showed him the photograph of dad.

01:14:20.489 --> 01:14:25.404
And he had the exact same photo, and he said
his father and my father are one in the same.

01:14:45.309 --> 01:14:46.111
This photo?

01:14:50.440 --> 01:14:51.080
Mm-hm.

01:14:52.072 --> 01:14:56.080
Well, I knew the day would come when
I would have to explain this to you.

01:14:57.572 --> 01:15:01.026
I told you the story about how
your father and I eloped, didn't I?

01:15:02.549 --> 01:15:04.283
And do you remember where we used to live?

01:15:04.309 --> 01:15:08.463
Downtown in that second floor apartment,
with the balcony off the living room?

01:15:09.738 --> 01:15:12.407
We were newly married, and I was pregnant with you.

01:15:12.423 --> 01:15:17.760
And your dad was away at sea a lot, and I
was working on my degree, studying very hard.

01:15:18.589 --> 01:15:22.711
I was determined to do well in
school, in case something happened.

01:15:27.430 --> 01:15:32.883
Our lives were already complicated when
your father returned home one night with a baby.

01:15:33.245 --> 01:15:33.766
Hey.

01:15:39.584 --> 01:15:40.225
Welcome...

01:15:41.566 --> 01:15:42.426
Yuichiro.

01:15:42.587 --> 01:15:43.715
Whose baby is that?

01:15:44.707 --> 01:15:45.926
He's Tachibana's.

01:15:46.387 --> 01:15:47.355
We need to take him.

01:15:47.871 --> 01:15:48.387
What?

01:15:49.488 --> 01:15:53.504
Tachibana was killed in an
accident aboard a repatriation ship.

01:15:54.168 --> 01:15:57.683
His poor wife died from complications during childbirth.

01:15:58.065 --> 01:16:00.480
The rest of his family was killed at Nagasaki.

01:16:01.402 --> 01:16:04.066
I won't have this child sent to an orphanage.

01:16:05.803 --> 01:16:10.715
Your father had legally adopted a
newborn baby without even asking me.

01:16:11.289 --> 01:16:15.426
The war had just ended, and things
like this were happening everywhere.

01:16:16.683 --> 01:16:21.691
Still, there was just no way I could
give the child the love and care he deserved.

01:16:22.210 --> 01:16:26.308
One of Yuichiro's friends recently
lost a child, so we gave the baby to him.

01:16:27.936 --> 01:16:28.652
How is he?

01:16:28.904 --> 01:16:30.402
Tell me, is he doing well?

01:16:31.970 --> 01:16:32.621
Mm-hm.

01:16:33.680 --> 01:16:34.574
I'm glad.

01:16:36.351 --> 01:16:40.480
Your father was impulsive, but he
always did what he thought was right.

01:16:41.332 --> 01:16:44.722
It was a relief to see the
baby end up with a loving family.

01:16:46.121 --> 01:16:51.463
Are you absolutely sure that Shun
couldn't possibly be dad's real son?

01:16:52.721 --> 01:16:54.557
I don't think I ever considered it.

01:16:55.603 --> 01:16:56.588
Why do you ask?

01:16:57.323 --> 01:16:59.659
Don't tell me he actually looks like your father?

01:17:04.072 --> 01:17:04.729
Mm-hm.

01:17:10.550 --> 01:17:15.082
Oh, Umi, sweetheart.

01:17:46.750 --> 01:17:47.293
See you tonight.

01:17:47.309 --> 01:17:47.897
Yeah, mom.

01:17:47.913 --> 01:17:48.756
See you tonight.

01:17:48.890 --> 01:17:50.141
Have a great day, girls.

01:18:37.846 --> 01:18:38.629
Hm.

01:18:53.564 --> 01:18:55.506
Hello again, Mr. Chairman, and welcome.

01:18:55.810 --> 01:18:57.474
Yeah, yeah.

01:18:58.450 --> 01:18:59.326
Hm.

01:19:22.223 --> 01:19:24.982
Never knew this existed under all that dust.

01:19:25.045 --> 01:19:25.602
Oh, yes, sir.

01:19:25.602 --> 01:19:26.912
They've done a good job.

01:19:28.605 --> 01:19:30.975
And what is your club studying, young man?

01:19:31.066 --> 01:19:31.490
Sir!

01:19:31.896 --> 01:19:34.903
The Astronomy Club has been studying
sunspots for the last ten years, sir.

01:19:34.903 --> 01:19:36.709
Oh, the last ten years, huh?

01:19:36.890 --> 01:19:39.373
Tell me, what discoveries have you made?

01:19:39.666 --> 01:19:43.256
That the sun is very, very old,
and our lifespans very, very short.

01:19:43.748 --> 01:19:45.584
No discoveries so far, sir!

01:19:46.485 --> 01:19:47.615
Honest answer.

01:19:54.605 --> 01:19:55.781
Philosophy Club?

01:19:56.645 --> 01:20:00.106
Seems to me you could really
benefit from a brand new clubhouse.

01:20:01.169 --> 01:20:03.606
And something nice for your junior members.

01:20:03.890 --> 01:20:08.270
We as human beings have complicated
every simple gift of the gods!

01:20:08.435 --> 01:20:09.856
Quoting Diogenes?

01:20:14.488 --> 01:20:18.213
I must say, principal, these students
of yours are very, very impressive.

01:20:18.658 --> 01:20:20.603
I'm gonna take a little look inside.

01:20:20.619 --> 01:20:21.579
Shun Kazama?

01:20:21.595 --> 01:20:22.174
Yes?

01:20:24.774 --> 01:20:25.787
Where's Plato?

01:20:26.042 --> 01:20:27.927
And what's that dog doing in there?

01:20:29.490 --> 01:20:30.291
Hello, dad?

01:20:30.324 --> 01:20:31.085
What's wrong?

01:20:31.248 --> 01:20:33.865
The third man in that photo is here at the harbor.

01:20:34.044 --> 01:20:36.177
I know he can tell you about your father.

01:20:36.598 --> 01:20:37.172
Huh?

01:20:37.382 --> 01:20:40.341
But his ship is leaning at... oh, 4:00!

01:20:40.767 --> 01:20:42.371
And he'll be away for several months.

01:20:42.387 --> 01:20:43.130
Get here!

01:20:43.263 --> 01:20:44.279
Get here fast!

01:20:55.275 --> 01:21:04.578
If the world should sink beneath the sea,
reach out your hand and find a friend in need.

01:21:04.664 --> 01:21:12.633
Brave the storm with head held
high, stand together side by side.

01:21:14.727 --> 01:21:23.617
Just like the mighty mountains
rising high above the fields.

01:21:24.172 --> 01:21:32.586
If we all stand together, then there
is nothing that will make us yield.

01:21:32.977 --> 01:21:42.363
If the world should sink beneath the sea,
reach out your hand and find a friend in need.

01:21:42.402 --> 01:21:51.582
Brave the storm with head held
high, stand together side by side.

01:21:53.531 --> 01:21:57.688
Students, while I am very impressed with your dedication,

01:21:57.797 --> 01:22:01.531
it doesn't change the fact that a new building is needed.

01:22:03.799 --> 01:22:08.377
So, I guess that makes it my job
to find a different place to put it.

01:22:14.598 --> 01:22:15.599
Yes!

01:22:15.615 --> 01:22:17.381
Yes!

01:22:17.857 --> 01:22:18.615
Thank you!

01:22:18.818 --> 01:22:19.818
Thank you, sir!

01:22:21.290 --> 01:22:22.708
Hooray!

01:22:22.950 --> 01:22:24.202
Hooray!

01:22:26.783 --> 01:22:28.701
On to the next experiment.

01:22:28.726 --> 01:22:29.384
Yeah!

01:22:30.046 --> 01:22:32.726
None of this would have happened without our goddess, Umi.

01:22:33.331 --> 01:22:33.706
Mm-hm.

01:22:33.706 --> 01:22:36.265
Thanks, but I really didn't do anything.

01:22:36.554 --> 01:22:37.421
Oh, come on.

01:22:37.476 --> 01:22:39.601
Quit being so modest and say, you're welcome.

01:22:40.148 --> 01:22:41.850
You are heaven sent!

01:22:41.866 --> 01:22:42.835
Thank you, Umi.

01:22:43.429 --> 01:22:44.023
Thank you!

01:22:44.249 --> 01:22:46.327
She's our little angel, Umi.

01:22:47.553 --> 01:22:48.471
Umi!

01:22:48.471 --> 01:22:49.273
Huh?

01:22:50.485 --> 01:22:51.602
You have to come.

01:22:53.015 --> 01:22:54.069
He's so dreamy.

01:22:54.160 --> 01:22:55.078
Perfect couple.

01:22:55.103 --> 01:22:56.062
You're so lucky.

01:22:56.062 --> 01:22:56.866
Good luck!

01:22:58.351 --> 01:22:59.187
Sorry, sir.

01:22:59.936 --> 01:23:05.296
I'm certain Umi and Shun wish they could be here to thank
you personally, but urgent matters have taken them away.

01:23:05.844 --> 01:23:07.101
Urgent matters, huh?

01:23:07.474 --> 01:23:08.874
Ah, to be young.

01:23:13.863 --> 01:23:14.675
Hey, Shun!

01:23:15.425 --> 01:23:16.027
Gen!

01:23:16.386 --> 01:23:17.566
Can you give us a ride?

01:23:18.652 --> 01:23:19.480
Umi!

01:23:26.493 --> 01:23:27.314
Ah!

01:23:28.814 --> 01:23:30.847
Umi, don't you worry, and hang on.

01:23:30.872 --> 01:23:32.746
I'll get you there with time to spare.

01:23:43.528 --> 01:23:45.086
If we're gonna make it, we'd better run.

01:23:45.111 --> 01:23:45.611
OK.

01:23:45.636 --> 01:23:46.429
Thanks, Gen.

01:23:48.494 --> 01:23:50.266
Sorry I couldn't get you there, Umi!

01:23:57.915 --> 01:23:58.677
Shun!

01:23:58.833 --> 01:23:59.552
Hurry!

01:24:02.516 --> 01:24:02.980
Thanks.

01:24:32.139 --> 01:24:33.451
That's my dad's tug.

01:24:50.385 --> 01:24:51.102
Come on.

01:25:01.092 --> 01:25:02.585
The kids are here to see you, captain.

01:25:12.337 --> 01:25:14.214
Push our departure back by fifteen.

01:25:14.230 --> 01:25:14.633
Aye.

01:25:19.344 --> 01:25:22.578
So then, you're my good friend Tachibana's boy?

01:25:22.859 --> 01:25:23.281
Yes, sir.

01:25:24.242 --> 01:25:26.656
And you must be Sawamura's daughter.

01:25:27.088 --> 01:25:28.438
Pleasure to meet you both.

01:25:44.147 --> 01:25:45.564
Your name is Shun, right?

01:25:45.982 --> 01:25:46.509
Yes, sir.

01:25:46.802 --> 01:25:52.642
Your father was Hiros hi Tachibana, and that's
him sitting in the front row, fourth from the right.

01:25:52.907 --> 01:25:55.540
And sitting next to him is Sawamura.

01:25:56.822 --> 01:25:59.611
We were just like brothers, the three of us.

01:26:00.240 --> 01:26:02.571
Tachibana, you should take the seat of honor.

01:26:02.776 --> 01:26:03.540
But why me?

01:26:03.733 --> 01:26:05.152
Because you're our fearless leader.

01:26:05.168 --> 01:26:05.884
You belong there.

01:26:06.240 --> 01:26:08.314
If I'm your leader, we're in trouble.

01:26:11.446 --> 01:26:13.848
Don't be the hero and die before me, OK?

01:26:15.050 --> 01:26:16.074
Same goes for you.

01:26:17.054 --> 01:26:18.363
Gentlemen, hold still.

01:26:30.735 --> 01:26:33.101
They were the best friends a man ever had.

01:26:33.299 --> 01:26:34.968
I think about them every day.

01:26:35.388 --> 01:26:39.101
They were brave and honest, and
I'm honored to have known them.

01:26:40.447 --> 01:26:44.843
When I look at you, what I see is
the legacy of those two great men.

01:26:45.327 --> 01:26:48.288
And I know they would be very proud.